BB_guide_1-22.pdf?id=1097}}</ref>\n\n===NBA draftees===\nThe Racers have had 25 players selected in the [[NBA draft]], the first being Johnny Reagan by the Chicago Stags in 1948. Twice Murray State has had two players selected in the draft, in 1967 (Herb McPherson, San Diego [now Houston] Rockets, third round; Don Duncan, San Diego Rockets, 10th round) and 1971 (Hector Blondet, Portland Trail Blazers, fifth round; Ron Johnson, Baltimore Bullets [now Washington Wizards], ninth round). Here is a list of Racers picked in the draft that posted minutes in the NBA regular season:<ref>{{cite web|url=https://stats.nba.com/draft/history/|title=NBA Advanced Stats|work=NBA.com}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Marcus Brown Euroleague Final Four 2005.JPG|thumb|150px|Marcus Brown scored 2,236 points while at Murray State and retired in 2011 as the Euroleague's all-time leading scorer (2,715 points).]]\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#002144; color:white;\"\n| '''Year''' || '''Round''' || '''Pick''' || '''Overall Pick''' || '''Player''' || '''NBA Club''' \n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n| [[1966 NBA Draft|1966]] ||3 ||1 || 21|| [[Stew Johnson]]||  [[New York Knicks]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.basketballreference.com/draft/draftyear.htm?yr=1966&lg=N|title=1966 NBA Draft|work=BasketballReference.com|accessdate=23 March 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100326021901/http://www.basketballreference.com/draft/draftyear.htm?yr=1966&lg=N#|archive-date=2010-03-26|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n| [[1968 NBA Draft|1968]] ||2 ||7 || 21|| [[Dick Cunningham]]||  [[Phoenix Suns]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.basketballreference.com/draft/draftyear.htm?yr=1968&lg=N|title=1968 NBA Draft|work=BasketballReference.com|accessdate=23 March 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100412065911/http://basketballreference.com/draft/draftyear.htm?yr=1968&lg=N|archive-date=12 April 2010|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n| [[1970 NBA Draft|1970]] ||9 ||6 || 142|| [[Claude Virden]]||  [[Seattle SuperSonics]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.basketballreference.com/draft/draftyear.htm?yr=1970&lg=N|title=1970 NBA Draft|work=BasketballReference.com|accessdate=23 March 2010|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100421232235/http://basketballreference.com/draft/draftyear.htm?yr=1970&lg=N|archivedate=21 April 2010}}</ref>\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n| [[1989 NBA Draft|1989]] ||2 ||4 || 31 || [[Jeff Martin (basketball)|Jeff Martin]]||  [[Los Angeles Clippers]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.basketballreference.com/draft/draftyear.htm?yr=1989&lg=N|title=1989 NBA Draft|work=BasketballReference.com|accessdate=23 March 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100310224305/http://www.basketballreference.com/draft/draftyear.htm?yr=1989&lg=N|archive-date=10 March 2010|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n| [[1992 NBA Draft|1992]] ||2 ||14 || 41 || [[Popeye Jones]]||  [[Houston Rockets]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.basketballreference.com/draft/draftyear.htm?yr=1992&lg=N|title=1992 NBA Draft|work=BasketballReference.com|accessdate=24 March 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100310224315/http://www.basketballreference.com/draft/draftyear.htm?yr=1992&lg=N|archive-date=10 March 2010|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n| [[1996 NBA Draft|1996]] ||2 ||17 || 46 || [[Marcus Brown]]|| [[Portland Trail Blazers]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.basketballreference.com/draft/draftyear.htm?yr=1996&lg=N|title=1996 NBA Draft|work=BasketballReference.com|accessdate=24 March 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100310224330/http://www.basketballreference.com/draft/draftyear.htm?yr=1996&lg=N|archive-date=10 March 2010|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n| [[2013 NBA Draft|2013]] ||2 ||4 || 34 || [[Isaiah Canaan]]|| [[Houston Rockets]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://insider.espn.go.com/nbadraft/results/player/_/id/19777/isaiah-canaan|title=Isaiah Canaan 2013 NBA Draft Profile|work=ESPN.com|accessdate=28 June 2013}}</ref>\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n| [[2015 NBA Draft|2015]] ||1 ||14 || 14 || [[Cameron Payne]]|| [[Oklahoma City Thunder]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/nba/player/_/id/3064230/cameron-payne|title=Cameron Payne 2015 NBA Draft Profile|work=ESPN.com|accessdate=25 June 2015}}</ref>\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n| [[2019 NBA Draft|2019]] ||1 ||2 || 2|| [[Ja Morant]]||  [[Memphis Grizzlies]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nba.com/draft}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Retired numbers===\nThe Racers have retired ten numbers, the first in 1952 and the last in 2020.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#002144; color:white;\"\n| '''No.''' || '''Player''' || '''Years Played''' || '''Year Retired'''\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|3 || [[Isaiah Canaan]] || 2009\u20132013 || 2018\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|5 || [[Marcus Brown]] || 1992\u20131996 || 2010\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|12 || [[Ja Morant]] || 2017\u20132019 || 2020\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|15 || [[Jeff Martin (basketball)|Jeff Martin]] || 1985\u20131989 || 1989\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|16 || Garrett Beshear || 1950\u20131953 || 1953\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|19 || [[Howie Crittenden]] || 1952\u20131956 || 1956\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|20 || [[Johnny Reagan]] || 1945\u20131948 || 2003\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|21 || [[Bennie Purcell]] || 1949\u20131952 || 1952\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|26 || [[Joe Fulks]] || 1941\u20131943 || 2001 \n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|30 || Paul King || 1987\u20131991 || 1991\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|54 || [[Popeye Jones]] || 1988\u20131992 || 1992\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|}\n\n===Scoring leaders===\nThe Racers have had six players score over 2,000 points and 41 players score over 1,000 points during their careers.  [[Marcus Brown]] holds the record for the most points in a single game with 45 against Washington on December 16, 1995.  [[Jeff Martin (basketball)|Jeff Martin]] holds the record for the most points in a single season with 806 during the 1987\u201388 season.<ref name=MS12-13p82>{{cite book|title=2012-13 Murray State Racers Men's Basketball Media Guide|publisher=[[Murray State University]]|page=82|year=2012|url=http://goracers.com/documents/2012/11/11/12-13_MBB_guide_78-113.pdf?id=1100}}</ref>\n\n====Career scoring leaders====\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#002144; color:white;\"\n|'''Rank'''|| '''Player''' || '''Years Played''' || '''Points''' \n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|1 || [[Jeff Martin (basketball)|Jeff Martin]] || 1985\u201389 || 2,484\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|2 || [[Isaac Spencer]] || 1997\u20132001 || 2,248\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|3 || [[Marcus Brown]] || 1993\u201396 || 2,236\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|4 || [[Popeye Jones]] || 1988\u201392 || 2,057\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|5 || [[Isaiah Canaan]] || 2009\u201313 || 2,050\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|6 || [[Howie Crittenden]] || 1952\u201356 || 2,019\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|7 || Lamont Sleets || 1979\u201384 || 1,902\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|8 || Vincent Rainey || 1994\u201397 || 1,888\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|9 || Frank Allen || 1989\u201393 || 1,811\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|10 || Garrett Beshear || 1949\u201353 || 1,716\n|}\n<ref name=MS12-13p81>{{cite book|title=2014-15 Murray State Racers Men's Basketball Media Guide|publisher=[[Murray State University]]|page=78|year=2014 |url=http://goracers.com/documents/2014/11/13//14_15_MBB_Guide_69_98.pdf?id=2341}}</ref>\n\n==Postseason==\n\n===NCAA Tournament===\nThe Racers have appeared in 16 NCAA tournaments.  They received their highest ranking in the tournament in 2012 with a 6th seed.  They have an overall 4\u201316 record in tournament games.  [[Popeye Jones]] holds the single game scoring record with 37 points against Michigan State in 1990.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.espn.go.com/ncb/tournament/history/_/team1/6800|title=Murray State Racers Tournament History|year=2010|work=[[ESPN]]|publisher=ESPN Internet Ventures|accessdate=23 March 2010}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Murray State Racers|Year|Seed|Round|Opponent|Result}}\n|- align=\"center\"\n| [[1964 NCAA University Division Basketball Tournament|1964]] || || Quarterfinals || [[Loyola Ramblers men's basketball|Loyola (IL)]] || L 91\u2013101\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| [[1969 NCAA University Division Basketball Tournament|1969]] ||  ||Quarterfinals || [[Marquette Golden Eagles men's basketball|Marquette]] || L 62\u201382\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| [[1988 NCAA Division I Men's Basketball Tournament|1988]] || #14 || First Round<br>Second Round|| #3 [[1987\u201388 NC State Wolfpack men's basketball team|North Carolina State]]<br> #6 [[1987\u201388 Kansas Jayhawks men's basketball team|Kansas]]|| '''W''' 78\u201375<br>L 58\u201361 \n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| [[1990 NCAA Division I Men's Basketball Tournament|1990]] || #16 || First Round || #1 [[Michigan State Spartans men's basketball|Michigan State]] || L 71\u201375 <sup>OT</sup>\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| [[1991 NCAA Division I Men's Basketball Tournament|1991]] || #13 || First Round || #4 [[Alabama Crimson Tide men's basketball|Alabama]] || L 79\u201389\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| [[1992 NCAA Division I Men'