e 2011\u201312 season, ranking 9th in the AP Poll and 7th in the Coaches Poll.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#002144; color:white;\"\n| '''Year''' || '''AP Poll''' || '''Coaches Poll''' || '''Coach'''\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|1950\u201351 || 16 || || [[Harlan Hodges]]\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|1951\u201352 || 16 || || Harlan Hodges\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|1952\u201353 || 17 || || Harlan Hodges\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|1970\u201371 || 17 || || [[Cal Luther]]\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|[[1997\u201398 NCAA Division I men's basketball rankings|1997\u201398]] || 25 || || [[Mark Gottfried]]\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|[[2011\u201312 NCAA Division I men's basketball rankings|2011\u201312]] || 9 || 7 || [[Steve Prohm]]\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|[[2014\u201315 NCAA Division I men's basketball rankings#AP Poll|2014\u201315]] || 25 || 24 || Steve Prohm\n|}\n\n* The AP Poll and Coaches Poll rankings represent the highest rankings received during that season.<ref name=MS14-15p69>{{cite book|title=2014-15 Murray State Racers Men's Basketball Media Guide|publisher=[[Murray State University]]|page=69|year=2014|url=http://goracers.com/documents/2014/11/13//14_15_MBB_Guide_69_98.pdf?id=2341}}</ref>\n\n==Rivalries==\nMurray State's historic basketball rivalry is with nearby [[WKU Hilltoppers basketball|Western Kentucky]].  The two teams became archrivals during their time together in the Ohio Valley Conference.  Although the schools no longer share their conference affiliation (Western Kentucky joined the [[Sun Belt Conference]] in 1982 and [[Conference USA]] [[2010\u201313 Conference USA realignment|in 2014]]), the two schools keep the series alive every few years. The two teams have met in basketball 147 times.  The Racers' primary in-conference OVC rivalry is now with [[Austin Peay Governors basketball|Austin Peay State University]], a school closer geographically than WKU.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://southerntimesgirlsandsports.wordpress.com/2010/02/09/the-25th-greatest-college-basketball-program-in-the-south-murray-state-racers/ |title=The 25th Greatest College Basketball Program in the South: Murray State Racers &#124; Southern Times, Girls, and Sports |publisher=Southerntimesgirlsandsports.wordpress.com |date=2010-02-09 |accessdate=2015-06-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150707012053/https://southerntimesgirlsandsports.wordpress.com/2010/02/09/the-25th-greatest-college-basketball-program-in-the-south-murray-state-racers/# |archive-date=2015-07-07 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wkusports.com/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=5400&ATCLID=204861551 |accessdate=March 10, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101102052509/http://www.wkusports.com/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=5400 |archivedate=November 2, 2010 }}</ref><ref name=\"sports.espn.go.com\">{{cite web|url=http://sports.espn.go.com/espnmag/story?id=3865828 |title=A look at some of college basketball's lesser-known rivalries |publisher=Sports.espn.go.com |date=2009-01-29 |accessdate=2015-06-21}}</ref> In February 2009, ESPN The Magazine highlighted the Austin Peay-Murray State rivalry.<ref name=\"sports.espn.go.com\"/>\n\n==Coaches==\n\nThe Racers have had 16 different head coaches in their history.  [[Carlisle Cutchin]] has the most wins in school history with 267.  [[Steve Newton]] has won the most OVC Regular Season titles with four & the most OVC Tournament titles with three.  There have been 10 different coaches to win the OVC Coach Of The Year award for a combined 16 times.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:84%;\"\n|- style=\"text-align:center; background:#002144; color:white;\"\n| '''Coach''' || '''Years (Total)''' || '''Overall Record (Pct.)''' || '''OVC Record (Pct.)''' || '''20 Win Seasons (Best)''' || '''Notes''' \n|- style=