r:white;\"\n| '''Year''' || '''Player'''\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|1938 || Etheridge McKeel\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|1941 || Bob Salmons \n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|1943 || [[Joe Fulks]]\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|1951 || Garrett Beshear\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|1952 || [[Bennie Purcell]]\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|1956 || Howie Crittenden\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|1966 || [[Stew Johnson]]\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|1968 || [[Dick Cunningham]]\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|1989 || [[Jeff Martin (basketball)|Jeff Martin]]\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|1992 || [[Popeye Jones]]\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|1994 || [[Marcus Brown]]\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|2004 || [[Cuthbert Victor]]\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|2012 || [[Isaiah Canaan]]\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\" bgcolor=\"\"\n|2019 || [[Ja Morant]]\n|}\n<ref name=MS12-13p15>{{cite book|title=2012-13 Murray State Racers Men's Basketball Media Guide|publisher=[[Murray State University]]|page=15|year=2012|url=http://goracers.com/documents/2012/11/11/12-13_MBB_guide_1-22.pdf?id=1097}}</ref>\n\n===NBA draftees===\nThe Racers have had 25 players selected in the [[NBA draft]], the first being Johnny Reagan by the Chicago Stags in 1948. Twice Murray State has had two players selected in the draft, in 1967 (Herb McPherson, San Diego [now Houston] Rockets, third round; Don Duncan, San Diego Rockets, 10th round) and 1971 (Hector Blondet, Portland Trail Blazers, fifth round; Ron Johnson, Baltimore Bullets [now Washington Wizards], ninth round). Here is a list of Racers picked in the draft that posted minutes in the NBA regular season:<ref>{{cite web|url=https://stats.nba.com/draft/history/|title=NBA Advanced Stats|work=NBA.com}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Marcus Brown 